text: Kulanu, Hebrew: כולנו , meaning All of Us, was an Israeli political party. == Overview == Its ideology was centrist social liberal, and Zionist. It was interested mainly with economic matters. Its political leaders were Yifat Shasha-Biton and then Moshe Kahlon. Kulanu was founded as a branch of Likud in 2014 and rejoined Likud in July 2019. It participated in the Fourth Netanyahu Government with 10 seats, and since April 2019 with 4 seats. == Other websites == * Category:2014 establishments in Israel Category:2019 disestablishments in Asia Category:Former political parties in Israel Category:Zionist parties
